Course Info: Explain what factors to consider when making decisions about data collection.Discuss the difference between biased and unbiased data.Describe databases with references to their functions and components.Describe best practices for organizing data. Data Collection, Spreadsheet, Metadata, SQL, Data Ethics  Data types and structures, Data responsibility, Database essentials, Organize and protect data , Engage in the data community DataScience
Course Info Translate:
When making decisions about data collection, it is important to consider factors such as the purpose of the data, the sources of the data, the quality of the data, and the potential impact of the data on stakeholders. Biased data is data that is influenced by personal opinions or prejudices, while unbiased data is data that is free from such influences.

Databases are organized collections of data that are used to store, retrieve, and manage information. They typically consist of tables, fields, and records, and can be accessed and manipulated using a query language like SQL.

Best practices for organizing data include creating a clear and consistent naming convention, documenting data sources and definitions, establishing data quality standards, and regularly backing up data to prevent loss. It is also important to consider data ethics, data types and structures, data responsibility, and database essentials when organizing data.

Engaging in the data community and staying up to date on developments in the field of Data Science can also help ensure that data is organized and protected effectively.

Course Info: Describe generative AI and distinguish it from discriminative AI.Describe the capabilities of generative AI and its use cases in the real world.Identify the applications of generative AI in different sectors and industries.Explore common generative AI models and tools for text, code, image, audio, and video generation. Artificial Intelligence (AI), ChatGPT, Large Language Models (LLM), Natural Language Generation, Generative AI Introduction and Capabilities of Generative AI, Applications and Tools of Generative AI\xa0, Course Quiz, Project, and Wrap-up DataScience
Course Info Translate:
Generative AI is a type of artificial intelligence that focuses on creating new data or content, while discriminative AI focuses on categorizing or labeling existing data. Generative AI has the capability to generate new text, code, images, audio, and videos based on patterns it has learned from existing data.

In the real world, generative AI can be used for various purposes such as creating realistic images, generating human-like text, composing music, and even deepfake videos. It has applications in sectors like healthcare, finance, marketing, and entertainment.

Some common generative AI models and tools include ChatGPT, Large Language Models (LLM), and Natural Language Generation. These tools can be used for tasks like content creation, data augmentation, and creative writing.

Other related topics include artificial intelligence (AI), deep learning, neural networks, and machine learning. Some specific areas of focus within computer vision include image classification, object detection, and projects such as traffic sign classification for not quite self-driving cars.

Course Title: Introduction to FPGA Design for Embedded Systems
Course Info: Describe what an FPGA is and how this technology was developedDetermine how to select the best FPGA architecture for a given applicationUse state of the art software tools for FPGA development and solve critical digital design problems using FPGAs Primality Test, Verilog, Digital Design, Static Timing Analysis "Whats this programmable logic stuff anyway?  History and Architecture ", FPGA Design Tool Flow; An Example Design, FPGA Architectures:  SRAM, FLASH, and Anti-fuse, Programmable logic design using schematic entry design tools DataScience
Course Info Translate:
An FPGA is a Field-Programmable Gate Array, a type of integrated circuit that can be programmed after manufacturing. This technology was developed to provide flexibility in digital design by allowing users to configure the hardware to perform specific functions.

To select the best FPGA architecture for a given application, one must consider factors such as performance requirements, power consumption, and cost. State-of-the-art software tools are used for FPGA development, including tools for programming in languages like Verilog, performing digital design, and analyzing timing constraints.

The Primality Test, Verilog, Digital Design, Static Timing Analysis are some of the tools and techniques used in FPGA development. The book "What's this programmable logic stuff anyway? History and Architecture" provides a comprehensive overview of FPGA design principles and architectures. FPGA design tool flow is explained through an example design, and different FPGA architectures such as SRAM, FLASH, and Anti-fuse are discussed.

Overall, programmable logic design using schematic entry design tools is a key aspect of FPGA development in the field of Data Science.
Course Title Translate: Introduction to FPGA Design for Embedded Systems

Course Info Translate: Data visualizations are extremely valuable in the field of business analytics as they allow for complex data to be easily understood and interpreted. Tableau Public is a tool that can be used to preprocess data before creating visualizations. This includes combining data from multiple tables within the same data source, as well as integrating data from other sources. Preprocessing data is an important step in creating effective visualizations. Tableau Public offers features for preparing data, restructuring data, and working with multiple data sources. This tool is essential for those working in the field of data science.

AND "WHAT WORKS?" DataScience
Course Info Translate: Design thinking is a methodology for creative problem solving that involves a user-centered approach to generating innovative ideas. It involves steps such as problem solving, user-centered design, prototyping, and addressing social issues. Before beginning the design thinking process, it is important to ask questions such as "What is?" and "What if?" to foster a mindset for innovation. Additionally, it is important to ask "What wows?" and "What works?" to determine which ideas are likely to produce specific, desired outcomes.
Course Title Translate: Design Thinking for the Greater Good: Innovation in the Social Sector

Course Info: Describe when a linear regression model is appropriate to useRead in and check a data set's variables using the software R prior to undertaking a model analysis    Fit a multiple linear regression model with interactions, check model assumptions and interpret the output      Correlation And Dependence, Linear Regression, R Programming INTRODUCTION TO LINEAR REGRESSION, Linear Regression in R, Multiple Regression and Interaction, MODEL BUILDING DataScience
Course Info Translate: A linear regression model is appropriate to use when there is a linear relationship between the independent and dependent variables. In order to analyze a model, it is important to first read in and check the variables of a data set using the software R. After this, a multiple linear regression model with interactions can be fitted, the model assumptions can be checked, and the output can be interpreted. This process involves understanding correlation and dependence, linear regression, and using R programming. It is an introduction to linear regression, focusing on multiple regression and interaction, and the process of building a model in Data Science.
Course Title Translate: Linear Regression in R for Public Health

Course Info Translate: The Vertex AI Platform is a tool used to quickly build, train, and deploy AutoML machine learning models without the need to write any code. It is a platform that allows users to easily implement machine learning on Google Cloud by leveraging various tools and environments provided by Google. Best practices for implementing machine learning on Google Cloud include using tools such as Inclusive ML, BigQuery, APIs, and the Google Cloud Platform. Responsible AI best practices should also be considered when developing machine learning models. The course and series will cover topics such as what it means to be AI-first, how Google implements machine learning, machine learning development with Vertex AI and Vertex Notebooks, best practices for implementing machine learning on Vertex AI, and responsible AI development. The course will also provide a summary of DataScience.

Course Title: Introduction to Data Analytics for Business
Course Info: Describe the information lifecycle from events in the real world to business actions Recognize the types of events and characteristics that are often used in business analyticsExplain how the data is captured by source systems and stored using both traditional and emergent technologiesGain familiarity with relational databases and learn how to use a simple but powerful language called SQL to extract analytical data sets of interest Data Model, Data Quality, Data Analysis, SQL Data and Analysis in the Real World, Analytical Tools, Data Extraction Using SQL, Real World Analytical Organizations DataScience
Course Info Translate: The information lifecycle starts with events in the real world and leads to business actions. It involves recognizing different types of events and their characteristics commonly used in business analytics. Data is captured by source systems and stored using both traditional and emerging technologies. Understanding relational databases and using SQL to extract analytical data sets is important. Topics covered include data modeling, data quality, data analysis, SQL data and analysis in the real world, analytical tools, data extraction using SQL, and real world analytical organizations.
Course Title Translate: Introduction to Data Analytics for Business

Course Title: 1. 基礎知識：データはあらゆるところにある
Course Info: データ、データ分析、データ エコシステムなど、データ アナリティクスの主な概念を定義、説明する分析的思考を使った具体例を交えながら、分析的思考で自己評価をするデータ アナリティクスにおけるスプレッドシート、クエリ言語、データの可視化ツールの役割を理解する具体的な業務/職位を挙げて、データ アナリストの役割を説明する データ分析, SQL, データ クレンジング, スプレッドシート, データの可視化（DataViz） データ アナリティクスとは, 分析的思考とは, 素晴らしいデータの世界, 使うツールの準備, キャリアにおける無限の可能性 DataScience
Course Info Translate: Data analytics is the process of defining and explaining the main concepts of data, data analysis, and data ecosystems using analytical thinking, with specific examples. It involves self-assessment through analytical thinking, understanding the role of spreadsheets, query languages, and data visualization tools in data analytics, and providing specific job positions in which data analysts play a role. It includes data analysis, SQL, data cleansing, spreadsheets, data visualization (DataViz), the definition of data analytics, analytical thinking, the world of amazing data, preparing tools for use, and infinite possibilities in a career in Data Science.
